TIGO Tanzania and Tecno have partnered to boost further internet penetration in the country. The two yesterday introduced new mobile device into the market as part of the contribution in support and creating digital society. Tigoâ€™s corporate Communication Manager Ms Woinde Shisael said the initiative was aimed at increasing access to information hence supporting economic activities like agriculture and business. She said in Dar es Salaam that the initiative comes at the time when Tigo internet penetration in the country has reached over 23 million people. Tigo Tanzania has been operating in the country for the last 25 years. Tecno Communication Manager Mr Eric Mkomoya said that their partnership with the telco in launching Tecno Phantom 9 is important in boosting smartphone use.